  "prompt": "If you are a chief financial officer of a start up, is that an employee position?",
  "response": "Yes, as a Chief Financial Officer (CFO) of a startup, you are typically considered an employee of the company. This role involves being a key member of the executive team, responsible for managing the financial actions of the startup, including financial planning, management of financial risks, record-keeping, and financial reporting. \n\nIn many startups, the CFO might also hold equity in the company, which is common for senior positions in early-stage businesses. However, this position is generally classified as an employee role, differentiating it from independent contractors or consultants.",
